  "doc_id": "30961",
  "text": "We found higher incidence rates for the thigh area, similar to some reviewed studies. When groin injuries were added to thigh injuries, the incidence rate reached 33.3%, which demonstrated that 1 in every 3 injuries occurred in the thigh area. The possible causes for these results could be inadequate warm-up, improper rehabilitation of the previous injuries, strength differences in anteroposterior and mediolateral thigh muscle groups, inflexibility, and improper training techniques. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In our study, the lower extremity injury incidence among the Turkish National Men's Football Team was 80.6%, which differed from the literature, at 61-90%. [CITATION_3] The most common injury types in our study were contusions (32.4%), muscle strains (30.6%) and sprains (21.3%). These results showed similarities with other studies. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] In the treatment of injuries, physical therapy agents and rehabilitation were used primarily (89.8%).",
